Can we replace every occurrence of Host to remote PLDM terminus?
Done
For this to work, is it mandatory to receive entity association PDRs before sensor/effecter or fru recordset pdrs?
Yes, it is mandatory to receive  entity association PDRs first. It is working the same way as well.
Can you please resolve merge conflicts?
Also I would suggest you to create a separate commit for the FRU record set `entity_instance` change
@pavithra I have created a new patchiest for this at https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/pldm/+/66939/1. could you please take a look?
Done
Can we rename it properly? `updateContainerId`
Done

so , we are picking the changed container id from the entity association tree. does this mean that we are dictating that the order in which we receive PDR's from the remote PLDM terminus.

In order words, does this logic work if we dont receive the entity association PDR's first ? does the Spec indicate any ordering ? If not is this an IBM only thing ?

According to the the Spec DSP 0248, Section 11, figure 7. Container ID of the contained entity(Child entity) is the same as the container ID of the Parent entity . Hence there is a need for the entity assiciation PDR to be received first before the individual entities are received from the remote terminus, in order to assign the correct container id to the contained entity.

@manoj As per the Spec DSP 0248, Section 11.8 - <Designing Association PDRs for Monitoring and Control>, 

1) Identify the physical entities and assign them Entity Identification Information          values:
    a) Identify the topmost physical container entities and give them the containerID for "system".
    b) Assign each remaining physical entity a different containerID value using whatever approach works best for the implementation. (For example, containerID values could be assigned sequentially starting from 1, or 1000 if it necessary to have a value that is more readily distinguishable as a being a containerID.)
    
2) Create Entity Association PDRs for the physical-to-physical containment associations.

3) Create the Sensor PDR, Effecter PDR, or other PDRs that are associated with the physical entities, and set the Entity Identification Information based on the containment PDRs that were created earlier.

4) Create the PDRs for any logical entities and set the containerID value for the containing entity to the containerID for the appropriate physical container entities.

5) Create the Sensor PDR, Effecter PDR, or other PDRs that reference those logical entities. 


We are basically following the same.
@sagar - can you add this information(in an abstract way) as part of the commit message itself. Dont want the information buried in gerrit comments.
Done

if the Entity identification information (entity type, instance id, container id) of the PDR matches with the entity in the entity association tree then t->container_id and e.entity_container_id have same container id. Please correct my understanding here.
That's right.
